        <div class="mb-10" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-warm-black mb-6">Frequently asked questions</h2>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-warm-black mb-2">Does it work with Nepali language content?</h3>
              <p class="text-warm-600">Yes. AI-native search can index and search content in Devanagari script, Romanized Nepali, and English. It handles code-switching automatically, matching queries against content regardless of script or language.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-warm-black mb-2">What about voice search in Nepali?</h3>
              <p class="text-warm-600">Voice search requires speech-to-text as a preprocessing step. While Nepali speech recognition is still developing, the guide covers integration patterns for when reliable Nepali ASR becomes available.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-warm-black mb-2">How does it compare to building our own search?</h3>
              <p class="text-warm-600">Building AI-native search requires ML expertise, training data, and ongoing maintenance. For most Nepali businesses, using a platform like Zunkiree Search is faster and more cost-effective. The guide includes a detailed build vs. buy comparison.</p>
